                        No. 126 of July 25 from Grew to
                            Byrnes (file No. 800.00
                        Summaries/7–2545).</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv02</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d780</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">780</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-07-23T07:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-07-23T07:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-23T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-23T07:00:00-05:00" n="780" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d780">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Austria)/7–2345:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 780<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Political Adviser for Austrian Affairs</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_EJG1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Erhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d780fn1">The gist of this message was included in telegram
                        No. 126 of July 25 from <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">Grew</persName> to
                            <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName> (file No. 800.00
                        Summaries/7–2545).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Verona</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-23T14:00:00+02:00">July 23, 1945—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>126. July 21 <persName corresp="#p_K7">Koniev</persName> sent letter to United
                    States, British, and French commanders stating he had been instructed facilitate
                    occupation of various sectors Vienna by our forces. <persName corresp="#p_GMGAM1">Gruenther</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_WMGJ1">Winterton</persName>
                    <pb facs="0869" n="675" xml:id="pg_675"/> and <persName corresp="#p_CBGPRP1">Cherrière</persName> invited to Vienna meeting 1 p.m., July 24, to settle
                    problems discussed at July 16 conference re taking over and they have accepted.
                    US reconnaissance party moving to Vienna July 22 and July 24.</p>
                <p>Soviet began evacuating Styria July 22 but were not quite ready to move into
                    Upper Austria north of Danube. Soviet Genl who went to Linz for preliminary
                    arrangements was reported as most cooperative.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_EJG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Erhardt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
